==English==
==Pronunciation==
\Pro"to*col\
== Etimology==
[[F.]] protocole, [[LL.]] ''protocollum'', [[fr]].
[[Gr.]]  the first leaf glued to the rolls of papyrus and the
notarial documents, on which the date was written; prw^tos
the first (see [[Proto-]] +  [[glue]].]

===Noun===
'''protocol'''
#A rule which guides how an activity should be performed.
# The original copy of any writing, as of a deed, treaty, dispatch, or other instrument. --Burrill.
# The minutes, or rough draught, of an instrument or transaction.
# ([[Diplomacy]]):
:(a) A preliminary document upon the basis of which negotiations are carried on.
:(b) A convention not formally ratified.
:(c) An agreement of diplomatists indicating the results reached by them at a particular stage of a        negotiation.

== Vertb==
===Transitive===
To make a protocol of.
===Intransitive===

To make or write protocols, or first draughts; to issue protocols. --Carlyle.


